Midgaard is the continent's primary inland legitimacy engine, built at the convergence of three major trade corridors: north to the Great Northern Forest and Kowloon's delta ports via the Lantern Road, west to Kiess along Roc Road, and east toward the desert oasis settlements and pyramid frontier. Founded under the First Stone Accord as a fortified caravan exchange, Midgaard evolved through five institutional eras: road-security militia compacts (First Stone Accord), civic standardization with posted tariffs and lamp-lines (Lantern Reforms), arcane registry oversight and reliquary checkpoints (Violet Compact), militarized provisioning under emergency charter law (Ash-and-Iron Decades), and the current Continuity-versus-Reckoning political tension. The city is governed by layered institutions including the Magistrate Ledgerhouse, Guard Command, Temple of the Resounding Heart, Guild Concordat Halls, and Lantern Registry Clerks. Its deepest institutional guilt: the Violet Compact's registry apparatus classified condemned persons as "arcane material" and transferred them to the Spirebound Conclave's mountain laboratories — a transaction recorded in the Granite Arcade trade ledger as "forty iron bars and six condemned debtors" to "the mountain academy." This history drives the Continuity/Reckoning divide: Continuity factions favor archive sealing and procedural stability; Reckoning factions demand public archive access and accounting for the transferred dead.

